-- Bagfas Falls in Istanbul After 1st-Quarter Profit Drops 31%
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-05-04T15:47:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/bagfas-falls-in-istanbul-after-1st-quarter-profit-drops-31-1-.html
Bagfas Bandirma Gubre Fabrikalari AS (BAGFS) ,
a Turkish fertilizer producer, declined to the lowest level in a
week after reporting first-quarter profit slumped.  Bagfas dropped 3 percent to 193 liras at the close in
Istanbul, the weakest since April 26.  Net income plummeted 31 percent to 12.7 million liras ($7.2
million) from 18.4 million liras a year ago, Bagfas said in a
statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
